Data Analysis Projects: Sales Performance & Market Basket Analysis
📋 Project Overview
This repository contains two comprehensive data analysis projects that demonstrate my proficiency in Python, MySQL, and data-driven decision making. Both projects showcase end-to-end analytical workflows - from data generation and database management to advanced analytics and business recommendations.

🚀 Projects
1. Sales Performance Analysis (Customer Churn Prediction)
Objective: Predict customer attrition using historical behavior and transaction data to identify at-risk customers and develop retention strategies.

Key Features:

✅ Customer churn prediction using Random Forest & Logistic Regression

✅ 85% model accuracy in identifying potential churners

✅ 16+ engineered features including order frequency, recency, and customer lifetime metrics

✅ High-risk customer identification with probability scoring

✅ Actionable retention strategies and recommendations

Technologies Used:

Python (Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-learn)

MySQL Database

Machine Learning (Random Forest, Logistic Regression)

Data Visualization (Matplotlib, Seaborn)

2. Market Basket Analysis
Objective: Uncover frequently purchased product combinations using association rule mining to enable cross-selling and product bundling strategies.

Key Features:

✅ Implemented Apriori algorithm for association rule mining

✅ Analyzed 1000+ transactions with 50+ products across 8 categories

✅ Identified top product pairs with support, confidence, and lift metrics

✅ Cross-category association analysis

✅ 5 strategic recommendations for revenue optimization

Technologies Used:

Python (Pandas, NumPy, mlxtend)

MySQL Database

